
1st Step in Developing React Application

    Download and Install Node.js on your local computer
    Create a new React Application 

    Implement these commands in your Code Editor in this exact order 
    Open your code editor terminal
    
    Add the below script to create react, react-dom, and react-scripts....
    
    npx create-react-app your-folder-name

// This will make the newly created folder the active React Directory

cd your-folder-name

// This will run the React Application in your browser
// Start the development server

npm start

Ref:	https://reactjs.org/docs/create-a-new-react-app.html
https://www.w3schools.com/react/react_getstarted.asp 

2nd Step â€“ Stripping down and Cleaning up your project folders/files

Remove all the unwanted folders and files from the project
Restructure and Test your project

// Keep only the below list content
1.	Src Folder

  // In this folder, you should keep only this file
  a.	Index.js 
  
  Remove these references
  -	import './index.css';
  -	import App from './App';
  -	import * as serviceWorker from './serviceWorker';
  -	serviceWorker.unregister();

2.	Public Folder
    a.	Index.html

    Remove the unnecessary references keep only important ones
    -	Important Meta Tags
    -	Title
    -	The main <div> tag

3.	Remove the README.md file

4.	Remember: You can add any additional file to your project

5.	Test whether your project is WORKING
    a.	Make sure to delete the following code from the index.js file and add you own
      <React.StrictMode>
        <App />
      </React.StrictMode>
    
    b. Refresh the page and see whether it is work effectively
    

